{
  "texts": [
    "We choose a representative set of simple objects Irr C which contains the tensor unit 1.",
    "The total quantum dimension of C is D:= a∈Irr C d 2 a.",
    "The dual of an object x ∈ Ob C is denoted x * and its evaluation and coevaluation morphisms are ev x: x * ⊗ x → 1 and coev x: 1 → x ⊗ x *.",
    "For each a ∈ Irr C there is a unique ā ∈ Irr C such that ā is isomorphic to a *.The unitary structure consists of dagger maps †: C(x → y) → C(y → x) written as f → f †.",
    "Each morphism space C(x → y) is a Hilbert space with the trace inner product (f, g) tr:= tr{f † • g}.We freely use the graphical calculus to represent and manipulate morphisms of C. See [30, Chapter I.2] for a good introduction to the graphical calculus."
  ]
}